Not sure whether the long Persian frame should be deleted i.e. placed under # 3(see the document shared on the Google drive "Frames & Metaphors with missing fields"(i.e. Persian frame has not been defined adequately ) or at least- due to the length of the frame- should be renamed by changing the first part,the verbal element, of the frame to a noun such as mohayya saazi
  In most cases where the Persian frame -especially by using combined verbal elements are too long, those parts can be substituted by a non verbal synonym

